      "writtenOn": "2019-08-14T12:12:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, ideally they should.  I want to share the repograph tests with gitstore, since the tests exercise tricky cases.  Unfortunately, those tests need to import assert/require, which is disallowed in non-test packages by go/imports/imports_test.go.  So I needed to move the tests to this new testutils package.  But since repograph doesn\u0027t use interfaces, just Graph and Commit structs, go/git/repograph/testutils needs to have a dependency on go/git/repograph, which means that we can\u0027t have tests in go/git/repograph which call into go/git/repograph/testutils.  So I moved the tests here.  It was the only solution I could think of; if you know of a better one, I\u0027ll go that route.",
      "parentUuid": "10971a99_7fd3e2f1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 1,
        "endChar": 17
      },
